cz.cuni.mff.d3s.deeco.knowledge

Interface ISession

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    TransactionalSession

    public interface ISession
    Interface representing session, which is used for performing bulk of operations on the knowledge repository. It is used to guarantee data consistency in the knowledge repository.
    Author:
    Michal Kit

    • Method Summary

      Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      void begin()
      Function starts the session.
      void cancel()
      Function used to abort the session.
      void end()
      Function ends the session.
      boolean hasSucceeded()
      Function checks if the session has been successfully ended.
      boolean repeat()
      Function checks if the session should be repeated due to either it has not been started yet or an error which occurred during the session ending.

        Function starts the session.

        void end()
         throws SessionException
        Function ends the session.
        Throws:
        SessionException - thrown when the session is required to be stopped before its start

      • cancel

        void cancel()
            throws SessionException
        Function used to abort the session.
        Throws:
        SessionException - thrown when the session is canceled after it was ended

      • repeat

        boolean repeat()
        Function checks if the session should be repeated due to either it has not been started yet or an error which occurred during the session ending.
        Returns:
        true or false depending on the current session state
